1
00:00:07,333 --> 00:00:09,333
[man] Hey, get over here.

2
00:00:09,416 --> 00:00:10,500
Hey! [grunts]

3
00:00:10,583 --> 00:00:12,125
[men laughing, jeering]

4
00:00:12,208 --> 00:00:13,708
Ooh! Ooh! Ooh!

5
00:00:13,791 --> 00:00:15,000
- [grunting]
- [groans]

6
00:00:15,083 --> 00:00:17,916
- [laughter and jeering continue]
- [Reo] Hey.

7
00:00:19,375 --> 00:00:21,833
Do you get a kick out of
picking on the weak?

8
00:00:22,583 --> 00:00:24,583
[man 1] Huh? Who the hell are you?

9
00:00:24,666 --> 00:00:26,416
[man 2] You got a problem, do ya?

10
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:28,458
[men grunting, groaning]

11
00:00:28,541 --> 00:00:30,833
[eerie music playing]

12
00:00:30,916 --> 00:00:31,791
[whimpers]

13
00:00:36,541 --> 00:00:38,083
Just go away.

14
00:00:38,166 --> 00:00:41,458
Shinjo, I heard
you're a tae kwon do champion. Yes?

15
00:00:41,958 --> 00:00:44,583
I… [splutters]

16
00:00:44,666 --> 00:00:45,833
Will you be my teacher?

17
00:00:45,916 --> 00:00:47,625
Too late, I've quit that.

18
00:00:49,750 --> 00:00:51,583
Shinjo, I want

19
00:00:52,208 --> 00:00:53,416
to get stronger.

20
00:00:56,666 --> 00:00:58,666
[approaching sirens wailing]

21
00:01:13,083 --> 00:01:15,583
[sirens fades]

22
00:01:15,666 --> 00:01:17,666
[ominous music playing]

23
00:01:20,583 --> 00:01:24,500
Oh, shit.
This guy, he's gonna kill Shimura.

24
00:01:28,416 --> 00:01:30,416
[Toru crying]

25
00:01:31,041 --> 00:01:32,583
[gasps, grunts]

26
00:01:34,333 --> 00:01:35,750
I don't like the police.

27
00:01:36,750 --> 00:01:38,166
No one's getting in my way.

28
00:01:38,250 --> 00:01:40,250
[Shimura gasping]

29
00:01:40,708 --> 00:01:43,000
Don't you dare.

30
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:45,541
Leave him be.

31
00:01:48,375 --> 00:01:50,708
- [groans]
- [Toru] Shimura!

32
00:01:50,791 --> 00:01:53,083
That's enough! Tell him to go!

33
00:01:53,833 --> 00:01:56,875
[solemn choral music playing]

34
00:01:56,958 --> 00:01:59,083
Is he important to you?

35
00:02:00,916 --> 00:02:02,291
- If he is…
- [straining]

36
00:02:04,875 --> 00:02:06,625
…you'd better protect him.

37
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:11,000
[grunting]

38
00:02:11,083 --> 00:02:12,041
[gasping]

39
00:02:13,708 --> 00:02:16,541
- [cracking]
- [Shimura whimpering]

40
00:02:16,625 --> 00:02:19,416
[screaming]

41
00:02:20,958 --> 00:02:22,500
[Ogi] Now he can't use his calf kick.

42
00:02:22,583 --> 00:02:24,791
[Shimura gasping, whimpering]

43
00:02:28,166 --> 00:02:31,166
You've done enough! Please listen!

44
00:02:31,250 --> 00:02:33,583
He's trying to kill you, Shimura!

45
00:02:34,083 --> 00:02:35,916
[Shimura] Don't interfere.

46
00:02:37,916 --> 00:02:41,208
Shinjo. Satisfied? [gasping]

47
00:02:42,750 --> 00:02:46,166
Forcing my friend
to watch me get my ass kicked.

48
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:49,166
[sobbing]

49
00:02:49,250 --> 00:02:50,375
You aren't

50
00:02:51,291 --> 00:02:52,666
a psychopath.

51
00:02:55,791 --> 00:02:57,041
Let's be real.

52
00:02:58,333 --> 00:02:59,625
You're jealous…

53
00:03:00,958 --> 00:03:01,875
of us.

54
00:03:03,166 --> 00:03:05,541
You son of a bitch.

55
00:03:07,708 --> 00:03:09,125
Kanegon is the…

56
00:03:10,625 --> 00:03:13,208
only friend I've ever had.

57
00:03:16,041 --> 00:03:18,000
I will never forgive you…

58
00:03:21,208 --> 00:03:23,958
for hurting my friend

59
00:03:28,291 --> 00:03:29,916
You shut the fuck up!

60
00:03:30,958 --> 00:03:31,958
[grunts]

61
00:03:32,041 --> 00:03:33,083
[gasps]

62
00:03:33,583 --> 00:03:35,458
Shimura!

63
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:38,333
The stream must stop, Kanegon.

64
00:03:40,833 --> 00:03:42,291
[Reo] This is the end.

65
00:03:44,125 --> 00:03:46,250
The channel… is mine.

66
00:03:47,541 --> 00:03:49,625
[Toru sobbing]

67
00:03:54,791 --> 00:03:56,125
Stop it, now.

68
00:03:56,208 --> 00:03:58,625
What? It's been over a while.

69
00:03:59,208 --> 00:04:01,375
Please. End it. No more.

70
00:04:01,916 --> 00:04:04,916
- I told you I'm not…
- Come on, can't you see?

71
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:06,208
Shimura!

72
00:04:07,791 --> 00:04:10,208
[dramatic music playing]

73
00:04:10,291 --> 00:04:11,791
[panting]

74
00:04:15,541 --> 00:04:16,375
HE STOOD UP!

75
00:04:16,458 --> 00:04:17,666
GET HIM, SHIMURA!

76
00:04:19,875 --> 00:04:21,208
How an amateur…

77
00:04:21,875 --> 00:04:23,250
[breathing heavily]

78
00:04:24,125 --> 00:04:25,750
…can beat…

79
00:04:26,333 --> 00:04:27,583
Oh, my.

80
00:04:28,125 --> 00:04:29,458
You're really crazy.

81
00:04:31,083 --> 00:04:32,875
…a Tae kwon do fighter.

82
00:04:34,458 --> 00:04:37,500
You will die if you keep doing this.

83
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,583
[wheezing]

84
00:04:39,666 --> 00:04:40,875
Rule one.

85
00:04:43,875 --> 00:04:45,083
All right

86
00:04:48,416 --> 00:04:49,583
I will kill you.

87
00:04:50,208 --> 00:04:51,083
[sobbing]

88
00:04:55,583 --> 00:04:56,708
Just die!

89
00:05:00,333 --> 00:05:03,791
[TOU-KEI] <i>How an amateur can beat</i>
<i>a tae kwon do fighter.</i>

90
00:05:04,416 --> 00:05:05,333
<i>Rule one…</i>

91
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:11,208
<i>is to steal their kicks.</i>

92
00:05:12,791 --> 00:05:15,208
<i>Everything leads up to this technique.</i>

93
00:05:16,166 --> 00:05:18,666
[both grunting]

94
00:05:18,750 --> 00:05:22,375
<i>Grab onto the back of their collar</i>
<i>like you're holding a bag</i>

95
00:05:22,458 --> 00:05:25,083
<i>and lift them on to your shoulder.</i>

96
00:05:25,583 --> 00:05:26,541
[straining]

97
00:05:28,291 --> 00:05:30,541
Wow! Baseball choke!

98
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:33,708
[straining]

99
00:05:37,458 --> 00:05:39,458
[grunting]

100
00:05:48,375 --> 00:05:49,541
Go.

101
00:05:51,750 --> 00:05:52,583
WHOAAAAAA!!

102
00:05:52,666 --> 00:05:54,041
DON'T LOOSEN YOUR GRIP!

103
00:05:54,666 --> 00:05:55,625
Yes, Shimura!

104
00:05:55,708 --> 00:05:57,708
[straining]

105
00:06:00,166 --> 00:06:01,125
[Reo gasps for air]

106
00:06:01,208 --> 00:06:03,500
[straining ferociously]

107
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:09,500
[Shimura grunting, straining]

108
00:06:16,166 --> 00:06:17,291
[silent]

109
00:06:24,958 --> 00:06:26,541
[Shimura straining]

110
00:06:28,125 --> 00:06:30,041
[keyboard tapping]

111
00:06:31,083 --> 00:06:33,291
Knock out. Shimura won!

112
00:06:36,083 --> 00:06:37,083
Yes!

113
00:06:37,166 --> 00:06:38,708
Shimura you won!

114
00:06:38,791 --> 00:06:40,791
[fabric stretching]

115
00:06:42,666 --> 00:06:45,541
[Shimura straining]

116
00:06:46,500 --> 00:06:48,291
Pull him! He's knocked out!

117
00:06:51,041 --> 00:06:52,708
[Shimura gasping, straining]

118
00:06:52,791 --> 00:06:54,041
[Toru] The fight is over.

119
00:06:54,125 --> 00:06:55,958
- You have to stop!
- Shimura!

120
00:06:56,041 --> 00:06:57,541
- [Toru] Hey!
- [Aki] Shimura!

121
00:06:57,625 --> 00:06:59,583
If you don't let go, he'll die!

122
00:06:59,666 --> 00:07:00,875
Shimura!

123
00:07:00,958 --> 00:07:03,458
[all gasping]

124
00:07:03,541 --> 00:07:05,500
[Toru] Hey! Come here.

125
00:07:06,250 --> 00:07:08,791
- You did it!
- [Shimura continues gasping]

126
00:07:08,875 --> 00:07:10,291
You're really something.

127
00:07:10,375 --> 00:07:12,583
- [Shimura gasping]
- [Toru] Hey.

128
00:07:20,291 --> 00:07:23,250
[tense music playing]

129
00:07:23,333 --> 00:07:25,541
TAE KWON DO TOURNAMENT
WINNER REO SHINJO

130
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:34,250
CHAMPION
TAE KWON DO TOURNAMENT

131
00:07:34,333 --> 00:07:36,333
- Did I say you could touch it?
- Sorry.

132
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:41,291
Shinjo, you really are incredible.

133
00:07:41,375 --> 00:07:43,458
I suck at everything I do.

134
00:07:44,750 --> 00:07:47,500
I hope I can become a champion like you.

135
00:07:50,958 --> 00:07:52,416
- Last one.
- Let's go.

136
00:07:53,125 --> 00:07:54,000
[grunts]

137
00:07:54,083 --> 00:07:55,625
[gentle music playing]

138
00:07:55,708 --> 00:07:56,666
Thank you.

139
00:08:00,375 --> 00:08:02,250
- Hmm?
- Huh?

140
00:08:03,583 --> 00:08:04,625
Take it.

141
00:08:05,333 --> 00:08:06,916
No, Shinjo, this, this is yours.

142
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:10,708
Forget it. Put it on and try
to get a little stronger.

143
00:08:11,583 --> 00:08:12,791
Are you sure?

144
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:15,333
Thank you so much.

145
00:08:16,458 --> 00:08:19,875
I'll cherish it until I die. [laughs]

146
00:08:19,958 --> 00:08:21,833
[phone ringing]

147
00:08:24,666 --> 00:08:27,166
[man] <i>Takuma is</i>
<i>at the former Ikebe factory site.</i>

148
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:44,333
[gasping] Takuma!

149
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:46,583
Hey!

150
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:48,791
Hang in there!

151
00:08:48,875 --> 00:08:50,875
[unsettling music playing]

152
00:08:52,541 --> 00:08:59,333
[moaning] I'm sorry
I couldn't be strong enough.

153
00:09:06,166 --> 00:09:07,041
Hey.

154
00:09:08,666 --> 00:09:09,666
Wake up!

155
00:09:12,458 --> 00:09:14,333
I said… Wake up!

156
00:09:14,416 --> 00:09:15,333
Takuma!

157
00:09:25,916 --> 00:09:27,916
[unsettling music continues]

158
00:09:29,083 --> 00:09:31,083
[approaching siren wailing]

159
00:09:49,291 --> 00:09:52,166
[Toru] Hey, let's get out of here.
He'll kill us if he wakes up.

160
00:09:52,250 --> 00:09:54,208
We can't. He's passed out.

161
00:10:00,166 --> 00:10:01,166
Whoa!

162
00:10:04,375 --> 00:10:05,625
What the hell are you doing?

163
00:10:05,708 --> 00:10:09,208
Wait, listen.
He went a little overboard, that's all.

164
00:10:09,291 --> 00:10:11,416
Hey? No, I was desperate and I…

165
00:10:20,166 --> 00:10:22,458
[Reo] I never want to see your face again.

166
00:10:28,250 --> 00:10:30,791
Oh… my.

167
00:10:30,875 --> 00:10:33,416
That bastard is crazy.

168
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:37,000
He was… crying.

169
00:10:37,083 --> 00:10:38,250
[Toru] What?

170
00:10:38,333 --> 00:10:40,500
What are you talking about? As if.

171
00:10:40,916 --> 00:10:43,708
- [Shimura] Uh…
- [Toru] By the way, is your foot okay?

172
00:10:44,208 --> 00:10:45,750
[Shimura] Uh, I think so.

173
00:10:45,833 --> 00:10:46,750
Yeah?

174
00:10:52,041 --> 00:10:54,041
[eerie music playing]

175
00:11:00,291 --> 00:11:03,541
WAY MORE INTENSE THAN BAD FELLOWS!

176
00:11:03,625 --> 00:11:06,250
DON'T COMPARE THIS TO THAT STAGED SHOW

177
00:11:06,333 --> 00:11:09,750
VIRAL HIT IS THE REAL DEAL

178
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:11,500
BAD FELLOWS IS WASHED-UP

179
00:11:11,583 --> 00:11:12,916
[Eiji] I'm terribly sorry.

180
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:16,333
If only I had… dealt with them properly

181
00:11:20,291 --> 00:11:21,500
It doesn't matter.

182
00:11:23,916 --> 00:11:28,208
In fact, now…
things are getting interesting.

183
00:11:37,166 --> 00:11:38,208
[phone buzzing]

184
00:11:41,291 --> 00:11:43,458
[Ogi] <i>He won. He did great.</i>

185
00:11:43,541 --> 00:11:45,458
[sighs] Oh, thank God.

186
00:11:48,583 --> 00:11:50,375
Is he hurt?

187
00:11:50,458 --> 00:11:52,458
I wonder if he's okay.

188
00:11:55,958 --> 00:11:58,208
[Ogi] <i>He took a beating,</i>
<i>but he should be fine.</i>

189
00:11:59,041 --> 00:12:01,208
- [sighs]
- [door slams open]

190
00:12:04,041 --> 00:12:06,666
You're worried about a boy?

191
00:12:06,750 --> 00:12:07,750
IS HE HURT?

192
00:12:07,833 --> 00:12:08,958
HE TOOK A BEATING

193
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:13,083
It's because you're involved with him.
All those videos are circulating.

194
00:12:13,166 --> 00:12:14,083
HOT GIRLFRIEND!

195
00:12:14,166 --> 00:12:15,625
Well, you won't see him again.

196
00:12:15,708 --> 00:12:16,833
Why?

197
00:12:17,625 --> 00:12:18,666
Why can't I see him?

198
00:12:18,750 --> 00:12:22,333
Because he has no use
in your future whatsoever.

199
00:12:23,291 --> 00:12:24,958
- Not true.
- Asamiya!

200
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:29,291
You mustn't plan to see him again.

201
00:12:31,375 --> 00:12:32,291
I won't.

202
00:12:33,125 --> 00:12:34,375
I promise

203
00:12:36,708 --> 00:12:39,041
BARBER YASHIO

204
00:12:43,375 --> 00:12:45,000
- [taps key]
- [Aki gasps]

205
00:12:45,083 --> 00:12:46,166
1,012,054 SUBSCRIBERS

206
00:12:46,250 --> 00:12:48,208
[Shimura] We hit a million subscribers!

207
00:12:48,291 --> 00:12:49,500
What the hell?

208
00:12:49,583 --> 00:12:50,458
Yes!!

209
00:12:50,541 --> 00:12:53,041
[all exclaiming, laughing]

210
00:12:53,125 --> 00:12:54,666
Aki, Aki! What did we make?

211
00:12:55,541 --> 00:12:57,541
This time we got…

212
00:12:58,375 --> 00:12:59,333
Wow!

213
00:12:59,416 --> 00:13:01,583
1.78 million!

214
00:13:01,666 --> 00:13:07,041
Wait a minute. That means we raked in…
1,068,000 yen in one stream.

215
00:13:07,125 --> 00:13:08,875
We made over a million yen!

216
00:13:08,958 --> 00:13:13,208
Our revenue to date is 2.3 million.
Good on you! [laughs]

217
00:13:13,291 --> 00:13:14,125
Ah!

218
00:13:14,625 --> 00:13:15,916
AMOUNT DUE: 3.14M YEN

219
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:18,291
Do you suppose we can do it again?

220
00:13:18,375 --> 00:13:20,333
Oh, for sure we can.

221
00:13:20,416 --> 00:13:22,750
We're one of the popular streamers now.

222
00:13:23,250 --> 00:13:25,541
Our time is finally here.

223
00:13:26,041 --> 00:13:27,041
Are you excited?

224
00:13:27,125 --> 00:13:28,583
Of course I am!

225
00:13:28,666 --> 00:13:30,916
You'll see why at school, okay?

226
00:13:32,791 --> 00:13:35,333
- [triumphant string music playing]
- [indistinct chatter]

227
00:13:35,416 --> 00:13:37,291
[boy 1] Look! There's Shimura!

228
00:13:37,375 --> 00:13:40,208
- [students clamoring, squealing]
- [cameras clicking]

229
00:13:40,291 --> 00:13:42,291
[music swells]

230
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:50,916
[Toru] <i>Well, how does this feel?</i>

231
00:13:51,416 --> 00:13:53,916
[Shimura] <i>Yeah, it's not bad.</i>

232
00:13:54,791 --> 00:13:56,000
[Toru] <i>Listen up.</i>

233
00:13:56,791 --> 00:13:59,791
<i>This is</i>
<i>what the view from the top is like.</i>

234
00:14:01,541 --> 00:14:03,750
[stately choral music playing]

235
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,833
[Aki] You know, this is great.

236
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:17,250
I mean, the view.
It's better at the top, you know.

237
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:19,125
What? What do you mean?

238
00:14:19,625 --> 00:14:21,541
[giggles] Have you gone crazy?

239
00:14:22,041 --> 00:14:24,708
Hey, I followed your official account.
Follow me back?

240
00:14:24,791 --> 00:14:26,666
Can you follow me back too?

241
00:14:27,625 --> 00:14:31,458
You repulse me.
Turning to the Internet for friends?

242
00:14:33,666 --> 00:14:35,708
[laughs] I'm joking!

243
00:14:38,125 --> 00:14:39,916
[giggling] She said yes!

244
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:44,125
I watch your channel every day! [chuckles]

245
00:14:48,250 --> 00:14:49,750
[whooping]

246
00:14:53,291 --> 00:14:54,583
[Aki squealing]

247
00:14:56,541 --> 00:14:58,375
[Aki laughing] We're going to crash!

248
00:15:02,958 --> 00:15:07,083
[orchestral fanfare playing]

249
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:18,875
[music ends]

250
00:15:18,958 --> 00:15:20,916
[rock music playing softly over PA]

251
00:15:22,166 --> 00:15:24,666
[Toru] What's wrong?
Aren't you gonna buy them?

252
00:15:24,750 --> 00:15:26,541
Well, they're really…

253
00:15:26,625 --> 00:15:28,333
You need more shoes.

254
00:15:28,833 --> 00:15:31,833
You are allowed to buy it.
Right, Aki?

255
00:15:32,333 --> 00:15:34,666
People have free will. Let him decide.

256
00:15:34,750 --> 00:15:37,208
Of course, but… well…

257
00:15:37,958 --> 00:15:40,208
You'll tell Asamiya you like her,
won't you?

258
00:15:43,250 --> 00:15:44,083
Mm!

259
00:15:44,166 --> 00:15:47,166
Well, it would be rude
to confess to her with such ratty shoes.

260
00:15:47,250 --> 00:15:48,916
Don't you think? Yeah?

261
00:16:04,583 --> 00:16:07,833
Oh! What's going on here?

262
00:16:08,416 --> 00:16:10,166
It's just a present.

263
00:16:10,250 --> 00:16:12,208
Wait, is it for me?

264
00:16:12,708 --> 00:16:14,000
[inhales deeply]

265
00:16:16,458 --> 00:16:17,583
Shimura.

266
00:16:17,666 --> 00:16:20,666
Don't worry about it.
I got a bonus.

267
00:16:20,750 --> 00:16:21,916
No, it's not that.

268
00:16:22,416 --> 00:16:24,583
You're not doing anything illegal?

269
00:16:24,666 --> 00:16:25,833
Huh?

270
00:16:25,916 --> 00:16:27,208
Are you scamming people?

271
00:16:27,291 --> 00:16:30,125
Uh no, why would you think that?

272
00:16:30,208 --> 00:16:32,625
[chuckling] Oh, that's good!

273
00:16:33,125 --> 00:16:35,333
Oh, thank you. [gasps]

274
00:16:36,083 --> 00:16:38,625
- I'll cherish it.
- Mm! Hmm!

275
00:16:38,708 --> 00:16:40,375
So cute.

276
00:16:42,041 --> 00:16:45,041
[laughs]

277
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:49,041
Thanks for the meal.

278
00:16:51,541 --> 00:16:54,458
- But you've barely touched your food.
- I'm not hungry.

279
00:16:54,958 --> 00:16:56,958
- Are you getting sick?
- No.

280
00:16:57,041 --> 00:16:58,250
Then what's wrong?

281
00:16:58,750 --> 00:17:01,083
Don't tell me you have a crush on someone.

282
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:05,916
Hey, is it the blonde guy
or the black-haired guy?  Which one?

283
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,875
[Aki] That's harassment, you know.

284
00:17:07,958 --> 00:17:10,708
[jaunty music playing]

285
00:17:22,041 --> 00:17:23,166
[Shimura] I'll be

286
00:17:24,583 --> 00:17:27,416
back to work starting tomorrow.

287
00:17:28,500 --> 00:17:33,500
<i>Can we walk home together after work?</i>

288
00:17:35,083 --> 00:17:36,083
[sighs]

289
00:17:45,125 --> 00:17:46,291
[phone clicks]

290
00:17:46,791 --> 00:17:49,375
[shudders, gasps]

291
00:17:49,458 --> 00:17:53,666
[breathing deeply]

292
00:18:01,583 --> 00:18:03,291
So what's this simple job?

293
00:18:03,375 --> 00:18:04,375
[chuckles]

294
00:18:07,791 --> 00:18:10,000
- Well…
- [taps keyboard]

295
00:18:10,083 --> 00:18:10,958
Here.

296
00:18:12,041 --> 00:18:13,125
Pick anyone.

297
00:18:13,208 --> 00:18:14,791
CLIENT LIST

298
00:18:15,291 --> 00:18:16,500
BUSINESS OWNER

299
00:18:16,583 --> 00:18:17,708
CHIEF DIRECTOR

300
00:18:17,791 --> 00:18:19,791
[unsettling music playing]

301
00:18:20,916 --> 00:18:23,416
I don't… get it.

302
00:18:25,583 --> 00:18:29,541
These are all… our important sponsors.

303
00:18:39,583 --> 00:18:40,583
[knocking at door]

304
00:18:44,208 --> 00:18:46,333
- [Rumi] Yes?
- It's Watanabe.

305
00:18:52,541 --> 00:18:54,000
I'm sorry to make you wait.

306
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:56,458
Work went overtime.

307
00:19:01,416 --> 00:19:02,875
Are you nervous?

308
00:19:03,958 --> 00:19:04,916
Yes.

309
00:19:05,875 --> 00:19:07,000
That's all right.

310
00:19:07,500 --> 00:19:09,500
Everyone is on their first time.

311
00:19:10,375 --> 00:19:11,583
It's what I like.

312
00:19:13,458 --> 00:19:16,416
Here, have a drink. Hmm?

313
00:19:29,833 --> 00:19:31,291
It's tea?

314
00:19:31,375 --> 00:19:33,333
What made you think I'd let you?

315
00:19:33,416 --> 00:19:35,625
Alcohol for someone underage?

316
00:19:36,958 --> 00:19:37,875
[chuckles]

317
00:19:40,291 --> 00:19:43,916
You know, I have a daughter
who's the same age as you.

318
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:44,833
What?

319
00:19:44,916 --> 00:19:49,583
And all she does
is waste time on being in love.

320
00:19:50,333 --> 00:19:55,083
She should just listen to
all the wise things I say to her.

321
00:19:58,208 --> 00:19:59,375
[sets glass on table]

322
00:20:01,708 --> 00:20:02,791
But…

323
00:20:04,416 --> 00:20:08,958
you'll listen
to everything that I say to you.

324
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:10,708
Right? Hmm?

325
00:20:11,416 --> 00:20:13,500
- Hmm. [chuckles]
- [Rumi shudders]

326
00:20:14,125 --> 00:20:15,041
[Shimura] She quit?

327
00:20:15,125 --> 00:20:19,416
You didn't know about that?
Well, she quit about a month ago.

328
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:24,791
It's been a really tough month,
so no more long vacations for you, got it?

329
00:20:26,125 --> 00:20:29,541
Oh, by the way,
Shimura you're a streamer, aren't you?

330
00:20:29,625 --> 00:20:30,875
UNREAD

331
00:20:30,958 --> 00:20:32,083
To tell you the truth,

332
00:20:32,166 --> 00:20:34,791
I was thinking about
trying out streaming myself.

333
00:20:34,875 --> 00:20:36,208
- Hey!
- [bells jangle]

334
00:20:36,291 --> 00:20:38,166
[boss] What, you're taking off again?

335
00:20:38,708 --> 00:20:40,708
- [outgoing call ringing]
- [panting]

336
00:20:49,583 --> 00:20:53,208
[poignant music playing]

337
00:20:58,291 --> 00:20:59,291
[Kaho] <i>I won't.</i>

338
00:20:59,916 --> 00:21:01,458
I promise

339
00:21:04,666 --> 00:21:06,208
In exchange,

340
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:09,333
I have a favor to ask.

341
00:21:12,958 --> 00:21:16,250
Shimura's mom must be
exempt from medical fees.

342
00:21:18,958 --> 00:21:20,083
Please!

343
00:21:29,125 --> 00:21:31,125
[music fades]

344
00:21:38,125 --> 00:21:39,041
Shimura?

345
00:21:46,583 --> 00:21:48,583
[somber music playing]

346
00:22:36,500 --> 00:22:38,500
- [music fades]
- [insects buzzing]

347
00:22:38,583 --> 00:22:39,958
- [young Kaho] <i>Stop it!</i>
<i>- </i>[boys laugh]

348
00:22:40,041 --> 00:22:42,166
- [insects buzzing]
- Here! Here!

349
00:22:42,250 --> 00:22:44,333
[Kaho] Give it back to me!

350
00:22:44,416 --> 00:22:45,500
[boy grunts]

351
00:22:45,583 --> 00:22:47,291
Try and get this!

352
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:51,000
Let's go. [laughs]

353
00:22:51,083 --> 00:22:53,083
[crying]

354
00:22:56,333 --> 00:23:00,250
[sobbing]

355
00:23:00,333 --> 00:23:01,250
What's wrong?

356
00:23:05,250 --> 00:23:08,541
They threw away my key chain.

357
00:23:09,958 --> 00:23:12,125
[boy 2] Shimura! What are you doing?

358
00:23:12,625 --> 00:23:14,458
I'll catch up later.

359
00:23:14,541 --> 00:23:16,250
Don't be upset. We'll find it.

360
00:23:20,291 --> 00:23:23,000
[tender music playing]

361
00:23:46,250 --> 00:23:48,250
There it is! I found it!

362
00:23:50,583 --> 00:23:52,000
Thank you!

363
00:23:52,083 --> 00:23:53,375
Asamiya!

364
00:23:54,250 --> 00:23:57,416
What are you doing here?
You'll be late for your recital.

365
00:23:58,083 --> 00:23:59,166
[Kaho] I'm sorry.

366
00:23:59,250 --> 00:24:00,250
Let's go.

367
00:24:01,416 --> 00:24:04,000
[somber music playing]

368
00:24:04,083 --> 00:24:05,416
See you soon!8

369
00:24:08,333 --> 00:24:09,333
Hey!

370
00:24:10,333 --> 00:24:12,041
Is Shimura with you?

371
00:24:12,541 --> 00:24:13,458
He's not coming.

372
00:24:14,583 --> 00:24:16,916
His mom had to go to hospital.

373
00:24:17,666 --> 00:24:21,250
Here. Shimura told me to give it to you.

374
00:24:24,708 --> 00:24:27,250
[boy 1] Hey, there's
a cabbage white butterfly over there.

375
00:24:27,333 --> 00:24:28,958
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

376
00:24:33,083 --> 00:24:35,791
- [music fades]
- [sniffles]

377
00:24:39,583 --> 00:24:41,416
BE STRONGER!
VIRAL_HIT

378
00:24:47,875 --> 00:24:49,833
<i>BAD FELLOWS </i>gave us an offer?

379
00:24:49,916 --> 00:24:51,250
Yeah, it's crazy!

380
00:24:51,333 --> 00:24:53,416
I got a DM from their management.

381
00:24:53,916 --> 00:24:56,875
They said they want us
to meet Mr. Kuwata and talk!

382
00:24:56,958 --> 00:24:58,291
Is it real though?

383
00:24:58,375 --> 00:24:59,833
Look for yourself.

384
00:25:00,625 --> 00:25:02,333
BAD FELLOWS

385
00:25:03,125 --> 00:25:04,041
It's real?

386
00:25:04,125 --> 00:25:05,250
[Toru] Told you it's real.

387
00:25:05,333 --> 00:25:07,541
I have met him… before.

388
00:25:08,125 --> 00:25:09,625
What? When?

389
00:25:09,708 --> 00:25:11,333
Before my Shinjo match.

390
00:25:11,416 --> 00:25:12,916
- [Toru] Where?
- At my home.

391
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:15,333
Huh. About what?

392
00:25:16,791 --> 00:25:19,083
He wanted me to fight on his show.

393
00:25:19,875 --> 00:25:21,666
Why didn't you tell me?

394
00:25:21,750 --> 00:25:23,708
I wasn't interested.

395
00:25:23,791 --> 00:25:24,875
You idiot!

396
00:25:24,958 --> 00:25:26,625
This is a huge offer.

397
00:25:26,708 --> 00:25:29,291
<i>BAD FELLOWS </i>would make us
even more famous!

398
00:25:31,416 --> 00:25:33,291
Maybe I'll hear him out.

399
00:25:33,375 --> 00:25:37,000
[Toru] Nice. You're motivated now.
I don't know what had gotten into you.

400
00:25:37,083 --> 00:25:40,208
Nothing. I just wanna make money quickly.

401
00:25:40,708 --> 00:25:43,375
[Toru] That's the spirit.
That's what I like to hear.

402
00:25:43,458 --> 00:25:45,333
I'll set up a meeting for you.

403
00:25:46,750 --> 00:25:48,708
[tense music playing]

404
00:25:48,791 --> 00:25:51,208
ROPPONGI

405
00:25:58,875 --> 00:26:00,458
What a fancy place.

406
00:26:00,541 --> 00:26:03,625
He messaged us. Don't be intimidated.

407
00:26:05,875 --> 00:26:07,041
[footsteps approaching]

408
00:26:15,166 --> 00:26:17,708
Sorry to keep you waiting. After you.

409
00:26:24,791 --> 00:26:26,791
[tense music continues]

410
00:26:42,333 --> 00:26:44,833
[music fades]

411
00:26:49,208 --> 00:26:51,208
I am so honored.

412
00:26:51,291 --> 00:26:55,875
The famous <i>Viral Hit </i>came
all this way to see me.

413
00:26:56,375 --> 00:26:59,500
No. Thank <i>you </i>so much for the DM.

414
00:27:00,375 --> 00:27:03,833
Um, I hear you had
already offered Shimura to participate

415
00:27:03,916 --> 00:27:05,375
in the <i>BAD FELLOWS </i>tournament.

416
00:27:06,291 --> 00:27:07,250
Yeah.

417
00:27:07,333 --> 00:27:09,958
Okay, well, we will consider it

418
00:27:10,041 --> 00:27:13,541
depending on the opponent
you choose for us. Yes?

419
00:27:17,166 --> 00:27:19,375
I think that you're confused.

420
00:27:19,916 --> 00:27:20,791
What?

421
00:27:21,916 --> 00:27:25,875
Well, handing you a role
in our <i>BAD FELLOWS </i>tournament

422
00:27:25,958 --> 00:27:27,291
was not my plan.

423
00:27:29,916 --> 00:27:33,291
But we're interested
in acquiring <i>Viral Hit.</i>

424
00:27:33,375 --> 00:27:34,375
[tense music playing]

425
00:27:34,458 --> 00:27:36,916
It's true, isn't it? You need money.

426
00:27:38,250 --> 00:27:39,458
Wait just a minute.

427
00:27:39,541 --> 00:27:41,625
There's no way we can agree to this.

428
00:27:41,708 --> 00:27:43,750
<i>Viral Hit </i>is our channel.

429
00:27:43,833 --> 00:27:44,916
We won't give it away.

430
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:46,791
She's right, we can't sell it.

431
00:27:46,875 --> 00:27:49,500
These childish games won't work forever.

432
00:27:49,583 --> 00:27:52,125
- Huh? What did you say?
- Kanegon.

433
00:27:52,208 --> 00:27:56,666
Could it be you feel threatened
because we're getting popular?

434
00:27:58,375 --> 00:28:00,041
[chuckles] Threatened?

435
00:28:00,125 --> 00:28:04,166
[laughing]

436
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:08,541
Any moment, your channel can disappear.

437
00:28:09,041 --> 00:28:11,291
What should I be worried about?

438
00:28:13,666 --> 00:28:16,541
How about you remember where you belong.

439
00:28:18,208 --> 00:28:19,833
This is ridiculous.

440
00:28:20,541 --> 00:28:21,541
Let's go.

441
00:28:27,416 --> 00:28:29,041
[music fades]

442
00:28:31,541 --> 00:28:33,625
Tell me, how are you going?

443
00:28:34,708 --> 00:28:36,500
Each day it changes.

444
00:28:36,958 --> 00:28:39,791
And, my body often feels heavy.

445
00:28:41,916 --> 00:28:45,291
But I have to try and get well for my son.

446
00:28:46,250 --> 00:28:50,833
This cardigan… was a present from him.

447
00:28:50,916 --> 00:28:53,583
I have called you here…
to talk about your son.

448
00:28:54,291 --> 00:28:55,541
My son?

449
00:29:01,250 --> 00:29:04,125
[grunting and punching on video]

450
00:29:06,500 --> 00:29:08,375
[mom gasps] Shimura?

451
00:29:08,458 --> 00:29:09,291
[gasps]

452
00:29:09,375 --> 00:29:11,458
Your son has been making money
by fighting.

453
00:29:11,541 --> 00:29:12,375
[gasps]

454
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:15,125
He's fighting? [gasps]

455
00:29:15,208 --> 00:29:18,166
- [somber music playing]
- [grunting on video]

456
00:29:18,250 --> 00:29:22,708
And because of your son,
my daughter, she was publicly humiliated.

457
00:29:23,416 --> 00:29:28,041
There are false rumors on social media
that they are seeing each other.

458
00:29:28,958 --> 00:29:30,500
Even her face is exposed.

459
00:29:31,625 --> 00:29:33,791
It's very troubling for us.

460
00:29:39,083 --> 00:29:42,166
I'll waive your medical expenses.

461
00:29:42,791 --> 00:29:43,666
Hey?

462
00:29:43,750 --> 00:29:50,208
In return, your son…
must never visit my daughter again.

463
00:29:58,041 --> 00:30:01,708
Sorry for the trouble
my son has caused you all.

464
00:30:01,791 --> 00:30:04,041
I'm truly sorry.

465
00:30:06,791 --> 00:30:07,916
But…

466
00:30:09,458 --> 00:30:10,833
I can't make that promise.

467
00:30:12,333 --> 00:30:14,416
Who he wants to see…

468
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:19,041
and who he wants to talk to…

469
00:30:20,041 --> 00:30:22,625
it's not my right to decide that for him.

470
00:30:25,291 --> 00:30:27,250
[grunting]

471
00:30:29,125 --> 00:30:29,958
[sighs]

472
00:30:30,041 --> 00:30:32,375
[tense music playing]

473
00:30:32,958 --> 00:30:35,375
- What happened to your face?
- Huh?

474
00:30:35,458 --> 00:30:38,250
Oh, you weren't fighting
with anyone were you?

475
00:30:38,791 --> 00:30:40,583
No, I would never do that.

476
00:30:41,750 --> 00:30:44,708
Don't worry about it. I got a bonus.

477
00:30:49,875 --> 00:30:51,208
[music fades]

478
00:30:55,458 --> 00:30:57,583
[Toru] That guy was a real asshole.

479
00:30:57,666 --> 00:31:01,416
Since it's come to this,
let's take down <i>BAD FELLOWS </i>by ourselves.

480
00:31:01,500 --> 00:31:06,750
But that guy seemed to know
that Shimura was in need of more money.

481
00:31:06,833 --> 00:31:09,500
Mm. He also knows where I live.

482
00:31:09,583 --> 00:31:12,458
Well, it's fine.
We won't have anything to do with him.

483
00:31:12,541 --> 00:31:14,166
Let's find our next opponent.

484
00:31:15,458 --> 00:31:17,708
- Huh?
- What is it?

485
00:31:20,208 --> 00:31:22,291
- The hell is this?
- What?

486
00:31:22,375 --> 00:31:24,833
[tense electronic music playing]

487
00:31:25,500 --> 00:31:27,000
They banned our account.

488
00:31:27,083 --> 00:31:27,916
SUSPENDED

489
00:31:29,333 --> 00:31:30,458
Huh?

490
00:31:30,541 --> 00:31:31,916
What the hell is going on?

491
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:35,958
[Shimura] I don't know, I don't know.
Wait, what if I try to open it again?

492
00:31:36,041 --> 00:31:37,750
Kanegon, what is it?

493
00:31:37,833 --> 00:31:38,875
Look at this.

494
00:31:41,583 --> 00:31:42,458
NEW PARTNERSHIP

495
00:31:42,541 --> 00:31:44,875
[Shimura] The platform we're using
and Kuwata's company

496
00:31:44,958 --> 00:31:46,708
formed a business partnership?

497
00:31:47,583 --> 00:31:51,000
[huffs] He did this. That bastard!

498
00:31:55,208 --> 00:31:56,250
[music fades]

499
00:31:57,458 --> 00:32:00,291
[Eiji sighs] Why did you leave?

500
00:32:00,375 --> 00:32:02,791
You left our important sponsor behind.

501
00:32:02,875 --> 00:32:04,333
[trembling] Sponsor?

502
00:32:04,416 --> 00:32:09,541
- You tried to pimp me out.
- Rumi, that's no way to put things.

503
00:32:10,041 --> 00:32:13,208
It's an important part
of business hospitality, you know?

504
00:32:13,291 --> 00:32:14,416
I don't get it.

505
00:32:15,500 --> 00:32:16,500
Enough.

506
00:32:17,500 --> 00:32:18,541
I quit.

507
00:32:18,625 --> 00:32:20,916
If it's like this, I'll go it alone.

508
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:22,041
Well, maybe.

509
00:32:23,666 --> 00:32:25,333
But the thing is…

510
00:32:25,416 --> 00:32:26,250
What?

511
00:32:26,333 --> 00:32:29,625
You haven't met your quota
and your contract isn't up yet.

512
00:32:30,166 --> 00:32:34,000
If you're going to go,
there's a penalty to pay.

513
00:32:34,083 --> 00:32:36,000
Can you afford that?

514
00:32:37,291 --> 00:32:38,541
That's what I thought.

515
00:32:40,083 --> 00:32:41,250
Okay, fine.

516
00:32:42,458 --> 00:32:45,541
[chuckles] How about online? Hmm?

517
00:32:46,333 --> 00:32:48,333
You won't have to sleep with old men,

518
00:32:48,416 --> 00:32:50,708
and you can edit your face
so no one will recognize you.

519
00:32:51,916 --> 00:32:52,958
Well?

520
00:32:54,500 --> 00:32:55,583
Sorry.

521
00:32:57,000 --> 00:32:58,208
I have to go home.

522
00:32:59,541 --> 00:33:02,041
- [gasping]
- Where are you going?

523
00:33:03,125 --> 00:33:04,000
Huh?

524
00:33:04,875 --> 00:33:05,958
To the cops?

525
00:33:06,458 --> 00:33:07,666
[inhales sharply]

526
00:33:11,875 --> 00:33:14,958
[moaning on video]

527
00:33:24,791 --> 00:33:27,833
Is that… a good idea?

528
00:33:27,916 --> 00:33:29,041
You think?

529
00:33:31,166 --> 00:33:34,375
This will end up on the Internet.

530
00:33:34,875 --> 00:33:38,958
[laughing]

531
00:33:39,041 --> 00:33:41,041
[indistinct chatter]

532
00:33:42,041 --> 00:33:44,041
[somber music playing]

533
00:33:53,041 --> 00:33:53,958
[inhales sharply]

534
00:33:55,208 --> 00:33:56,833
[Toru] What are you doing over there?

535
00:33:56,916 --> 00:33:58,916
[distant pop music playing]

536
00:34:00,916 --> 00:34:03,416
You're not doing
something bad again, are you?

537
00:34:07,375 --> 00:34:08,375
[gasps]

538
00:34:11,333 --> 00:34:13,125
Your agency was behind it?

539
00:34:15,083 --> 00:34:18,625
<i>It wasn't you that had</i>
<i>those two guys attack Shimura?</i>

540
00:34:19,125 --> 00:34:20,125
No.

541
00:34:21,375 --> 00:34:24,083
We're in the same agency,
but I've never met them.

542
00:34:24,166 --> 00:34:26,458
And you didn't get me drunk
and steal our password?

543
00:34:26,541 --> 00:34:28,833
Uh, I apologize for the password.

544
00:34:29,916 --> 00:34:30,958
I'm sorry.

545
00:34:31,041 --> 00:34:32,666
Ah, jeez.

546
00:34:34,125 --> 00:34:36,833
But why would the president do that?

547
00:34:39,791 --> 00:34:44,416
Our agency falls…
under the <i>BAD FELLOWS </i>group is why.

548
00:34:45,083 --> 00:34:46,083
Huh?

549
00:34:48,208 --> 00:34:52,458
He DM'd me to get close to <i>Viral Hit,</i>
I suppose.

550
00:34:53,625 --> 00:34:55,625
Really? You think so?

551
00:34:55,708 --> 00:34:58,083
He was looking for <i>Viral Hit</i>.

552
00:34:58,166 --> 00:35:00,958
He seemed to be
under the big boss's thumb.

553
00:35:03,125 --> 00:35:04,333
[sighs]

554
00:35:05,416 --> 00:35:07,583
I don't know if I can trust you.

555
00:35:08,333 --> 00:35:10,875
After all that you put me through.

556
00:35:12,666 --> 00:35:14,083
I'm sorry.

557
00:35:15,833 --> 00:35:18,166
[groans] Fine, I'll trust you.

558
00:35:20,083 --> 00:35:20,916
All right.

559
00:35:22,208 --> 00:35:24,208
Let's go fix this.

560
00:35:24,291 --> 00:35:26,875
We'll go to the police
and tell them everything.

561
00:35:33,375 --> 00:35:34,375
[gasps]

562
00:35:48,833 --> 00:35:50,833
[pensive music playing]

563
00:35:56,916 --> 00:35:58,125
[no in-scene audio]

564
00:36:19,541 --> 00:36:21,541
[music intensifies]

565
00:36:30,416 --> 00:36:32,416
[music fades]

566
00:36:32,500 --> 00:36:34,666
So is it really bad?

567
00:36:35,375 --> 00:36:39,791
She's been undergoing radiation therapy.
It's not working.

568
00:36:40,708 --> 00:36:42,750
And the immunotherapy,

569
00:36:42,833 --> 00:36:45,500
I may be able to give you the money soon.

570
00:36:45,583 --> 00:36:48,708
Uh, look, in her current condition,
it just wouldn't be effective.

571
00:36:49,583 --> 00:36:51,000
So, what?

572
00:36:52,208 --> 00:36:53,083
[gasps]

573
00:36:53,958 --> 00:36:57,208
Uh, what… what can be done for her?

574
00:36:57,291 --> 00:36:59,416
Well, there is iron radiotherapy.

575
00:36:59,500 --> 00:37:02,708
- Use it. Please.
- It's a very expensive treatment.

576
00:37:02,791 --> 00:37:04,708
Yes, okay. I'll work and pay for it.

577
00:37:04,791 --> 00:37:08,375
We would do it several times
to see if it was effective.

578
00:37:09,541 --> 00:37:11,125
How much is it?

579
00:37:11,208 --> 00:37:12,541
In total,

580
00:37:13,208 --> 00:37:15,458
somewhere around ten million.

581
00:37:16,833 --> 00:37:18,375
So much.

582
00:37:19,541 --> 00:37:22,416
However, we do understand
your family situation.

583
00:37:22,500 --> 00:37:24,125
The director suggested to your mother

584
00:37:24,208 --> 00:37:28,000
she could be exempt
from the medical expenses, but…

585
00:37:28,583 --> 00:37:29,458
What?

586
00:37:48,708 --> 00:37:51,333
Are you okay, Mom?

587
00:37:52,458 --> 00:37:53,750
I'm okay.

588
00:37:54,541 --> 00:37:56,083
Don't look so sad.

589
00:38:01,875 --> 00:38:03,291
I was shocked.

590
00:38:05,625 --> 00:38:08,041
I didn't know what you were doing.

591
00:38:10,291 --> 00:38:11,208
Huh?

592
00:38:12,791 --> 00:38:14,083
I'm sorry.

593
00:38:15,333 --> 00:38:19,166
I'm sorry about saying
who would watch your stream.

594
00:38:23,208 --> 00:38:24,916
It's so popular.

595
00:38:27,125 --> 00:38:29,458
You have many fans on there.

596
00:38:30,250 --> 00:38:31,208
I'm proud of you.

597
00:38:33,958 --> 00:38:35,958
[gentle music playing]

598
00:38:36,583 --> 00:38:38,583
[crying]

599
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:41,208
Thank you.

600
00:38:44,708 --> 00:38:45,958
[sighs]

601
00:38:48,083 --> 00:38:49,750
I have to say…

602
00:38:51,541 --> 00:38:55,000
I don't really like seeing you
get beaten up like that.

603
00:38:56,833 --> 00:38:59,041
Even less, do I like

604
00:38:59,791 --> 00:39:02,250
you beating someone else.

605
00:39:05,000 --> 00:39:05,833
[sniffles]

606
00:39:10,375 --> 00:39:11,583
You're right.

607
00:39:14,333 --> 00:39:15,833
But it's strange…

608
00:39:17,375 --> 00:39:18,625
Somehow,

609
00:39:19,958 --> 00:39:21,500
I did feel good.

610
00:39:23,583 --> 00:39:26,583
My son, who always seemed a bit fragile,

611
00:39:28,041 --> 00:39:29,416
looked strong.7

612
00:39:31,500 --> 00:39:34,291
[crying]

613
00:39:34,375 --> 00:39:35,666
[mom] I thought

614
00:39:37,291 --> 00:39:40,625
he might be okay,
even if I'm not around anymore.

615
00:39:42,500 --> 00:39:44,416
[crying]

616
00:39:45,208 --> 00:39:46,791
Why do you say that?

617
00:39:47,500 --> 00:39:48,416
Mm…

618
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:50,791
[inhales]

619
00:39:51,458 --> 00:39:53,500
I'm just telling you my thoughts.

620
00:39:53,583 --> 00:39:55,583
[weeping]

621
00:40:06,666 --> 00:40:08,541
- [phone buzzing]
- [sniffles]

622
00:40:12,291 --> 00:40:13,666
[sniffles]

623
00:40:13,750 --> 00:40:14,708
<i>Moshi moshi.</i>

624
00:40:14,791 --> 00:40:15,958
[Toru] <i>Shimura.</i>

625
00:40:16,833 --> 00:40:19,416
<i>It was all Kuwata's doing after all.</i>

626
00:40:20,250 --> 00:40:21,791
And the ban wasn't it.

627
00:40:22,583 --> 00:40:26,333
He was… targeting us from the very start.

628
00:40:27,833 --> 00:40:30,791
[breathes deeply]

629
00:40:43,083 --> 00:40:45,375
[doors open, close]

630
00:40:50,125 --> 00:40:51,541
So, what is it?

631
00:40:51,625 --> 00:40:53,000
It was you, wasn't it?

632
00:40:53,583 --> 00:40:55,916
You got <i>Viral Hit</i>'s account banned.

633
00:40:56,000 --> 00:40:59,291
I told you,
you should remember your place.

634
00:40:59,791 --> 00:41:01,958
I know what you've been doing
behind the scenes.

635
00:41:02,041 --> 00:41:03,375
So, what do I care?

636
00:41:03,458 --> 00:41:05,916
We can expose you in a video
anytime we want.

637
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:07,791
Fine, go do it.

638
00:41:07,875 --> 00:41:09,458
[tense music playing]

639
00:41:09,541 --> 00:41:12,208
What do you think of this instead?

640
00:41:14,166 --> 00:41:16,791
I'll give you
a fight purse of a million yen.

641
00:41:16,875 --> 00:41:20,916
Consider it.  This will be
your last chance to work for me.

642
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:22,416
What do you mean by that?

643
00:41:22,500 --> 00:41:25,291
- We're not going to agree--
- No. This simplifies it.

644
00:41:26,875 --> 00:41:30,375
If I make an appearance now,
it'll generate buzz.

645
00:41:30,458 --> 00:41:32,333
This is my proposal.

646
00:41:33,458 --> 00:41:35,541
- I want to fight.
- Shimura!

647
00:41:35,625 --> 00:41:37,000
I don't want your money.

648
00:41:38,166 --> 00:41:41,625
For this, in exchange, I want donations.

649
00:41:42,625 --> 00:41:44,375
Donations?

650
00:41:44,458 --> 00:41:47,333
We'll divide into a red and a blue corner

651
00:41:47,416 --> 00:41:50,416
and viewers will donate
to the side they want to support.

652
00:41:50,500 --> 00:41:53,500
<i>BAD FELLOWS </i>will be
the ones streaming the match.

653
00:41:53,583 --> 00:41:55,541
It's a good deal, isn't it?

654
00:41:55,625 --> 00:41:57,750
[tense music continues]

655
00:41:59,541 --> 00:42:00,875
The rules, then.

656
00:42:01,375 --> 00:42:03,250
<i>BAD FELLOWS' </i>own rules.

657
00:42:03,333 --> 00:42:05,583
Three five-minute rounds.

658
00:42:06,833 --> 00:42:08,208
Will that work for you?

659
00:42:08,916 --> 00:42:10,291
I think it does.

660
00:42:11,375 --> 00:42:12,625
Works for me.

661
00:42:13,416 --> 00:42:16,250
I will find an opponent
that's worthy of you.

662
00:42:18,375 --> 00:42:20,083
There's no need to do that.

663
00:42:22,750 --> 00:42:25,375
[music swells]

664
00:42:25,458 --> 00:42:27,125
You'll be the one fighting.

665
00:42:27,875 --> 00:42:31,541
You bastard. Who do you think you are?

666
00:42:32,500 --> 00:42:34,916
The <i>BAD FELLOWS </i>representative.

667
00:42:35,500 --> 00:42:38,250
Wouldn't this match
get them the most attention this way?

668
00:42:39,083 --> 00:42:40,541
Or are you afraid

669
00:42:41,541 --> 00:42:45,375
that you're less popular
and the donations will expose it?

670
00:42:49,166 --> 00:42:50,000
Very well.

671
00:42:50,083 --> 00:42:51,375
[militant music playing]

672
00:42:51,458 --> 00:42:54,041
Let's do it. Me and you.

673
00:42:59,250 --> 00:43:00,708
Donations?

674
00:43:00,791 --> 00:43:04,250
Our account may be banned,
but we've got a million fans.

675
00:43:04,333 --> 00:43:06,666
What if they <i>all </i>donated?

676
00:43:07,583 --> 00:43:09,666
Ten million could be done.

677
00:43:10,625 --> 00:43:12,250
Nice going, Shimura!

678
00:43:12,333 --> 00:43:15,541
- What a brilliant idea!
- Gross! Get off me!

679
00:43:16,750 --> 00:43:20,125
Okay, let's strategize
how we can appeal to our fans

680
00:43:20,208 --> 00:43:21,916
in a meeting at Aki's house.

681
00:43:22,000 --> 00:43:24,583
Oh, I can't. I have plans.

682
00:43:24,666 --> 00:43:27,125
- You what?
- Just some errands.

683
00:43:31,958 --> 00:43:33,333
I came to return this.

684
00:43:33,416 --> 00:43:36,166
[video game characters grunting]

685
00:43:38,791 --> 00:43:39,958
I'll leave you be.

686
00:43:41,958 --> 00:43:43,416
Account got banned, didn't it?

687
00:43:46,125 --> 00:43:47,041
Yeah.

688
00:43:48,125 --> 00:43:49,250
Why was that?

689
00:43:51,500 --> 00:43:53,166
<i>BAD FELLOWS </i>is the reason.

690
00:43:55,833 --> 00:43:59,500
And now,
Shimura's planning to fight the big boss.

691
00:44:02,791 --> 00:44:03,750
Kuwata.

692
00:44:06,875 --> 00:44:09,000
I wouldn't do that.

693
00:44:11,125 --> 00:44:12,375
Why shouldn't he?

694
00:44:13,208 --> 00:44:16,708
[hip-hop music playing]

695
00:44:20,458 --> 00:44:21,875
TEACH HIM A LIFE LESSON!

696
00:44:21,958 --> 00:44:23,833
PUNISH THE DISRESPECTFUL BRATS!

697
00:44:23,916 --> 00:44:26,791
<i>♪ Runs in my bones</i>
<i>Scream under the light, this moment… ♪</i>

698
00:44:26,875 --> 00:44:27,958
[sighs] Mm.

699
00:44:28,041 --> 00:44:31,625
[music fades]

700
00:44:32,583 --> 00:44:35,083
[eerie music playing]

701
00:44:35,166 --> 00:44:37,166
[indistinct chatter]

702
00:44:39,208 --> 00:44:40,875
- [boys laughing]
- [Aki] Hey!

703
00:44:41,375 --> 00:44:42,291
Hey!

704
00:44:42,875 --> 00:44:44,208
Watch this.

705
00:44:44,291 --> 00:44:45,250
[sighs]

706
00:44:45,333 --> 00:44:47,541
[girls squealing on video]

707
00:44:47,625 --> 00:44:49,250
What? [gasps]

708
00:44:49,333 --> 00:44:51,250
VIRAL HIT PRODUCER
CAUGHT UNDERAGE DRINKING

709
00:44:51,333 --> 00:44:52,541
[Toru] No way.

710
00:44:53,500 --> 00:44:55,625
[students laughing, chattering]

711
00:44:55,708 --> 00:44:56,916
Is that Kanegon?

712
00:44:58,833 --> 00:45:00,000
Look at this.

713
00:45:01,625 --> 00:45:03,458
- Is that him?
- Kanegon!

714
00:45:04,750 --> 00:45:06,708
[laughter continues]

715
00:45:07,791 --> 00:45:09,000
SO FULL OF HIMSELF

716
00:45:11,458 --> 00:45:13,541
THEIR ACCOUNT DESERVES TO BE BANNED

717
00:45:14,125 --> 00:45:15,458
A HIGH-SCHOOL DRUNK LOL

718
00:45:16,083 --> 00:45:17,375
A WOMANIZING BRAT

719
00:45:17,458 --> 00:45:20,750
[man] Viral Hit <i>is facing major backlash.</i>

720
00:45:20,833 --> 00:45:22,750
<i>The channel launched</i>
<i>in February this year.</i>

721
00:45:22,833 --> 00:45:26,958
<i>It became popular for showing real fights</i>
<i>picked by a high school student</i>

722
00:45:27,041 --> 00:45:29,208
<i>and has earned lots of money</i>
<i>from donations.</i>

723
00:45:29,291 --> 00:45:32,583
<i>However, the producer's drinking video</i>
<i>has gone viral</i>

724
00:45:32,666 --> 00:45:34,333
<i>and is facing major backlash.</i>

725
00:45:34,416 --> 00:45:37,000
<i>The channel is facing</i>
<i>a storm of criticism.</i>

726
00:45:37,083 --> 00:45:39,000
<i>Their fighter is</i>
<i>high school student Kota Shimura.</i>

727
00:45:39,083 --> 00:45:40,166
BLOOD MONEY LOL

728
00:45:40,250 --> 00:45:42,750
<i>Producer and cameraman is Toru Kaneko.</i>

729
00:45:42,833 --> 00:45:43,833
I WANT MY MONEY BACK

730
00:45:43,916 --> 00:45:46,166
<i>The editor is a female student</i>
<i>who attends the same school.</i>

731
00:45:46,250 --> 00:45:47,833
VIRAL HIT IS FINISHED

732
00:45:48,583 --> 00:45:49,416
ARREST INEVITABLE

733
00:45:49,500 --> 00:45:52,958
[Toru] Damn it. This must be his doing.
Kuwata must be pulling the strings.

734
00:45:53,041 --> 00:45:56,375
Kuwata is a former MMA champion
in underground fighting.

735
00:45:56,458 --> 00:45:57,333
How do you know that?

736
00:45:57,416 --> 00:45:58,500
Shinjo told me.

737
00:45:58,583 --> 00:46:00,166
- Shinjo told you?
- And that's not all.

738
00:46:00,250 --> 00:46:04,000
He saw Kuwata at the scene
where his friend died.

739
00:46:04,500 --> 00:46:06,625
- [tense music playing]
- [clock ticking]

740
00:46:10,375 --> 00:46:12,958
[Aki] Shinjo is convinced
that Kuwata is the murderer.

741
00:46:13,791 --> 00:46:15,625
What does this all mean?

742
00:46:15,708 --> 00:46:18,875
Shinjo got a call
on the day his friend was killed.

743
00:46:18,958 --> 00:46:21,666
The caller told him
where his friend was being attacked.

744
00:46:22,916 --> 00:46:25,416
But it was a trap to frame Shinjo.

745
00:46:25,500 --> 00:46:29,208
- Why would Kuwata kill Shinjo's friend?
- I don't know.

746
00:46:29,291 --> 00:46:33,166
But… this proves
how dangerous Kuwata really is.

747
00:46:34,166 --> 00:46:37,791
So we can't expect a lot of donations.
We should back out of the fight.

748
00:46:37,875 --> 00:46:39,791
Well, what else can I do here?

749
00:46:40,791 --> 00:46:43,083
You know I need the money.

750
00:46:44,166 --> 00:46:46,708
I have no way to make money any other way.

751
00:46:47,208 --> 00:46:48,958
I really have no choice left.

752
00:46:49,041 --> 00:46:49,916
Hmm.

753
00:46:50,000 --> 00:46:52,208
- [camera clicks]
- [man 1] This is the real deal!

754
00:46:52,291 --> 00:46:53,375
- It's <i>Viral Hit!</i>
<i>- </i>[laughter]

755
00:46:53,458 --> 00:46:55,250
[Toru] Hey!
Don't film us without permission.

756
00:46:55,333 --> 00:46:57,208
- [man 1] You gotta get owned!
- [man 2] Too late!

757
00:46:57,291 --> 00:46:58,541
Get lost!

758
00:46:58,625 --> 00:47:02,666
[sighs] We… stand out when we're together.

759
00:47:02,750 --> 00:47:05,791
Let's separate now,
and if anything happens, call me. Got it?

760
00:47:05,875 --> 00:47:07,875
- [somber music playing]
- [panting]

761
00:47:15,291 --> 00:47:16,500
[notifications bleeping]

762
00:47:16,583 --> 00:47:17,708
GOODBYE NORMAL LIFE LOL

763
00:47:17,791 --> 00:47:19,958
YOU'VE BEEN COMMITTING A CRIME

764
00:47:20,041 --> 00:47:22,833
WHO THINKS OF MAKING MONEY
THROUGH VIOLENCE? LOL

765
00:47:22,916 --> 00:47:25,083
I BET THE POLICE ARE ONTO THEM

766
00:47:25,166 --> 00:47:27,166
THEY WON'T GET AWAY WITH THIS

767
00:47:27,250 --> 00:47:30,750
TREMBLE WITH FEAR

768
00:47:31,250 --> 00:47:32,125
PAY US BACK

769
00:47:32,208 --> 00:47:33,041
I'LL KILL YOU

770
00:47:33,125 --> 00:47:34,000
HE'S THAT POOR?

771
00:47:34,083 --> 00:47:35,500
MOM'S HOSPITALIZED

772
00:47:35,583 --> 00:47:36,541
BAD PARENTING

773
00:47:36,625 --> 00:47:37,666
CLASS SHOWS

774
00:47:37,750 --> 00:47:38,833
YOU'RE DEAD, SHIMURA

775
00:47:38,916 --> 00:47:40,166
A CRIMINAL LIVES HERE

776
00:47:40,250 --> 00:47:41,291
PAY US BACK

777
00:47:42,916 --> 00:47:46,791
[man] This must be
where Shimura lives. [scoffs]

778
00:47:53,125 --> 00:47:54,750
GOLD DIGGER

779
00:47:54,833 --> 00:47:56,333
KANEGON'S THE MASTERMIND

780
00:47:56,416 --> 00:47:58,291
I'LL KILL KANEGON WITHIN A WEEK

781
00:47:58,375 --> 00:47:59,541
I'LL HUNT YOU DOWN

782
00:47:59,625 --> 00:48:01,625
[notifications bleeping]

783
00:48:16,125 --> 00:48:17,166
DIE

784
00:48:17,250 --> 00:48:19,375
[whirring]

785
00:48:23,250 --> 00:48:24,125
[Toru gasping]

786
00:48:32,708 --> 00:48:36,000
[whimpering, screaming]

787
00:48:36,083 --> 00:48:38,083
YOUR ACCOUNT HAS BEEN SUSPENDED

788
00:48:38,166 --> 00:48:39,625
[outgoing phone call ringing]

789
00:48:39,708 --> 00:48:42,000
THIS IS VIRAL HIT'S SCHOOL

790
00:48:42,083 --> 00:48:43,875
DROP DEAD SHIMURA!

791
00:48:43,958 --> 00:48:45,875
DIE, KANEGON

792
00:48:47,000 --> 00:48:48,208
There's no point.

793
00:48:48,291 --> 00:48:50,416
Kaneko won't even answer his phone.

794
00:48:50,500 --> 00:48:51,416
[Aki] <i>I see.</i>

795
00:48:51,500 --> 00:48:53,708
I can try calling him later.

796
00:48:54,791 --> 00:48:56,041
[Shimura] <i>Yeah, please do.</i>

797
00:48:57,708 --> 00:48:59,916
Are you… doing okay?

798
00:49:00,000 --> 00:49:00,875
Mmm.

799
00:49:01,625 --> 00:49:03,250
No turning back

800
00:49:04,083 --> 00:49:05,250
It's too late.

801
00:49:08,166 --> 00:49:09,125
Be careful.

802
00:49:09,791 --> 00:49:10,666
I will.

803
00:49:11,083 --> 00:49:11,916
And, you.

804
00:49:12,916 --> 00:49:13,791
Yeah.

805
00:49:14,958 --> 00:49:16,666
<i>Well, see you later.</i>

806
00:49:16,750 --> 00:49:17,875
[disconnect tone]

807
00:49:31,083 --> 00:49:32,291
AKI YASHIO

808
00:49:33,125 --> 00:49:35,500
- [phone ringing]
- [whimpering]

809
00:49:50,708 --> 00:49:54,083
Kuwata is a former MMA champion
in underground fighting.

810
00:49:54,166 --> 00:49:56,833
[Kuwata] <i>It's true, isn't it?</i>
<i>You need money.</i>

811
00:49:56,916 --> 00:50:01,166
[doctor] <i>In total,</i>
<i>somewhere around ten million.</i>

812
00:50:05,791 --> 00:50:06,916
It's okay.

813
00:50:07,416 --> 00:50:08,958
- I've got TOU-KEI.
- [keys tapping]

814
00:50:10,250 --> 00:50:11,666
NEWTUBE HOW_TO_FIGHT

815
00:50:11,750 --> 00:50:12,750
[taps key]

816
00:50:14,625 --> 00:50:15,458
What?

817
00:50:17,250 --> 00:50:18,666
What's going on?

818
00:50:18,750 --> 00:50:21,583
THIS CHANNEL HAS BEEN DELETED

819
00:50:23,000 --> 00:50:24,791
- I'm going out.
- What?

820
00:50:25,458 --> 00:50:27,041
Where are you going so late?

821
00:50:27,875 --> 00:50:29,583
[pensive music playing]

822
00:50:29,666 --> 00:50:31,250
I'm not going to let this happen.

823
00:50:32,750 --> 00:50:33,750
Aki!

824
00:51:01,083 --> 00:51:02,166
Logan.

825
00:51:07,416 --> 00:51:09,625
Where are you, TOU-KEI?

826
00:51:09,708 --> 00:51:12,500
I have no way of winning without you.

827
00:51:14,833 --> 00:51:16,208
[door buzzer sounds]

828
00:51:25,708 --> 00:51:27,041
Who's out there?

829
00:51:28,833 --> 00:51:30,041
It's Asamiya.

830
00:51:31,250 --> 00:51:32,083
What?

831
00:51:40,291 --> 00:51:42,041
[tires screech]

832
00:51:44,083 --> 00:51:45,166
[car door opens]

833
00:51:45,750 --> 00:51:47,458
[car doors slam]

834
00:51:47,541 --> 00:51:48,958
So, what do you want?

835
00:51:49,416 --> 00:51:50,291
Hey.

836
00:52:03,625 --> 00:52:04,833
Please

837
00:52:05,541 --> 00:52:07,541
don't take <i>Viral Hit </i>from us.

838
00:52:09,083 --> 00:52:10,416
That channel…

839
00:52:12,083 --> 00:52:15,250
it's a very important place for us.

840
00:52:15,333 --> 00:52:17,041
[poignant music playing]

841
00:52:17,125 --> 00:52:19,250
It's because we had that channel

842
00:52:20,916 --> 00:52:22,666
that all of us were saved.

843
00:52:23,333 --> 00:52:26,166
[sighs] So, please…

844
00:52:26,250 --> 00:52:28,500
[crying]

845
00:52:28,583 --> 00:52:30,041
Please, I'm begging you.

846
00:52:31,291 --> 00:52:34,500
Please give us back <i>Viral Hit</i>.

847
00:52:37,250 --> 00:52:38,375
What is it?

848
00:52:40,458 --> 00:52:43,875
I saw the hate
that you were getting online.

849
00:52:44,583 --> 00:52:46,875
Oh. Mm.

850
00:52:46,958 --> 00:52:51,833
You turned down the offer
to waive your mother's medical fees.

851
00:52:53,000 --> 00:52:55,250
- [Shimura] Mm.
- I asked my dad.

852
00:52:57,625 --> 00:52:59,083
But in return,

853
00:53:00,708 --> 00:53:02,541
I said I wouldn't see you again.

854
00:53:04,166 --> 00:53:05,000
No.

855
00:53:06,916 --> 00:53:09,833
If you don't have to worry
about the medical fees,

856
00:53:09,916 --> 00:53:12,208
you won't have to fight anymore.

857
00:53:12,833 --> 00:53:15,541
- Then, you won't get hate online--
- But I really can't accept that.

858
00:53:16,333 --> 00:53:19,625
Because I don't want to stop seeing you.

859
00:53:21,250 --> 00:53:22,750
Besides,

860
00:53:23,250 --> 00:53:26,166
it's not… just for money.

861
00:53:29,958 --> 00:53:31,916
I don't want to give it up.

862
00:53:33,291 --> 00:53:35,583
Everything we built together.

863
00:53:39,000 --> 00:53:39,875
[Aki sniffs]

864
00:53:40,916 --> 00:53:42,333
[crying]

865
00:53:42,416 --> 00:53:44,000
If I say no,

866
00:53:45,125 --> 00:53:46,166
what then?

867
00:53:50,583 --> 00:53:52,708
If you intend to crush us,

868
00:53:54,833 --> 00:53:56,500
we won't go easy on you either.

869
00:53:56,583 --> 00:54:00,708
[laughing]

870
00:54:02,583 --> 00:54:03,708
Oh, I see!

871
00:54:03,791 --> 00:54:05,166
[laughs]

872
00:54:05,250 --> 00:54:07,791
[sighs]

873
00:54:07,875 --> 00:54:10,250
You still don't understand, do you?

874
00:54:10,750 --> 00:54:14,083
Everything you have,
that you've built with sweat and tears,

875
00:54:14,166 --> 00:54:17,208
I can crush in a single day.

876
00:54:18,583 --> 00:54:23,166
No. In just a matter of minutes even.

877
00:54:23,875 --> 00:54:26,666
Everything you've built up to this point,

878
00:54:27,333 --> 00:54:30,125
was that insignificant in the end.

879
00:54:31,458 --> 00:54:34,375
[Kaho] You're going to do it
no matter what, right?

880
00:54:38,166 --> 00:54:39,000
But…

881
00:54:42,333 --> 00:54:44,791
you won't get
any more videos from TOU-KEI.

882
00:54:46,333 --> 00:54:47,750
What? How?

883
00:54:48,250 --> 00:54:50,625
How did you know about his videos?

884
00:54:51,125 --> 00:54:52,333
I sent them.

885
00:54:53,375 --> 00:54:55,166
The videos were sent by me.

886
00:54:56,791 --> 00:54:57,750
What?

887
00:54:57,833 --> 00:55:02,500
- [tense music playing]
- Oh, <i>Viral Hit… </i>is already dead.

888
00:55:03,083 --> 00:55:04,750
[laughing]

889
00:55:06,583 --> 00:55:08,458
It can't end.

890
00:55:08,541 --> 00:55:10,041
I won't let it.

891
00:55:10,541 --> 00:55:13,000
I'll protect it no matter what!

892
00:55:13,083 --> 00:55:17,750
Let me go! Let me go! I said let me go!

893
00:55:21,125 --> 00:55:22,666
The videos? I don't understand.

894
00:55:22,791 --> 00:55:24,791
- [tense music swells]
- [Kaho sighs]

895
00:55:26,833 --> 00:55:29,583
There are videos on there.

896
00:55:30,291 --> 00:55:32,041
And I've been sending them to you.

897
00:55:39,000 --> 00:55:41,166
BE STRONGER!
NEWTUBE @VIRAL_HIT

898
00:55:41,250 --> 00:55:43,708
Wait, so you know who TOU-KEI is?

899
00:55:43,791 --> 00:55:45,333
No, this isn't even mine.

900
00:55:46,625 --> 00:55:47,500
What?

901
00:55:48,250 --> 00:55:49,083
Then…

902
00:55:50,041 --> 00:55:52,958
was someone else watching those videos?

903
00:55:53,750 --> 00:55:56,625
BE STRONGER!
NEWTUBE @VIRAL_HIT

904
00:55:57,250 --> 00:55:58,625
[Aki] Let go of me.

905
00:55:58,708 --> 00:56:00,000
I said

906
00:56:00,083 --> 00:56:02,000
let go of me!

907
00:56:02,083 --> 00:56:03,458
[men grunting]

908
00:56:06,458 --> 00:56:08,375
You little…

909
00:56:12,750 --> 00:56:14,166
Don't hold back.

910
00:56:14,875 --> 00:56:17,916
I am the original <i>Viral Hit.</i>

911
00:56:18,500 --> 00:56:25,333
VIRAL HIT

912
00:56:30,708 --> 00:56:32,708
[rock music playing]

913
00:57:53,916 --> 00:57:54,916
[music ends]
